Fig. 4
 shows SEM images of BiOBr, g-C3N4, BiOBr/g-C3N4, and BiOBr/g-C3N4/CQDs., BiOBr had an irregular sheet-like structure with smooth edges (Fig. 4a) and g-C3N4 had a clear lamellar structure (Fig. 4b). The SEM image of the BiOBr/g-C3N4 photocatalyst is shown in Fig. 4c. Clearly, the incorporation of g-C3N4 resulted in the attachment of some small, irregular sheet-like structures onto the larger substrate sheet. Fig. 4d shows that the microstructure of the BiOBr/g-C3N4/CQDs catalyst was characterized by a stacked layer-by-layer arrangement of sheet-like structures with no significant changes. Energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDS) analysis showed that the BCC50 composite material contained C, N, Br, O, and Bi (Fig. 5
).
